  "published": "2020-08-25",
  "runtimeMin": 69,
  "format": "Sean, Amanda, and Chris react to DC FanDome's trailer haul, revisit 2011 at the movies, then run back the movie draft, snake-drafting six categories apiece.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "DC FanDome",
      "note": "trailers for Wonder Woman 1984, The Suicide Squad, The Batman, and the Snyder Cut",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Wonder Woman 1984",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "the trailer's Gal Gadot/Chris Pine screwball energy won everyone over; the one worry was Kristen Wiig's Cheetah playing too serious."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Suicide Squad",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "James Gunn's do-over of the 2016 film, with Idris Elba stepping in for Will Smith; the featurette leans on Viola Davis for its best moment."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Batman",
          "year": 2022,
          "note": "Matt Reeves' trailer, scored to a Nirvana song, delivered exactly the noir detective take everyone had already guessed at, and it worked anyway."
        },
        {
          "title": "Zack Snyder's Justice League",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "the 'Snyder Cut,' four hours split into episodes, set to Leonard Cohen's 'Hallelujah' over old Justice League footage."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "2011, revisited",
      "note": "before the draft, a look back at the year in movies",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "J. Edgar",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Amanda's awkward almost-date with her now-husband, before they'd really met: 'a tough break for everyone involved.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "Hugo",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "another one Amanda remembers seeing with him early on."
        },
        {
          "title": "We Bought a Zoo",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Cameron Crowe; Amanda wrote a full blog post about it."
        },
        {
          "title": "My Week with Marilyn",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "not particularly memorable, per Amanda."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Dilemma",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "second-tier Ron Howard, by Amanda's own ranking."
        },
        {
          "title": "Cowboys & Aliens",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Jon Favreau, in a rough year."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Help",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "part of what Sean calls one of the most treacherous Best Picture slates of the century."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Artist",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "the Best Picture winner, and 'one of the last great Harvey Weinstein jobs.'"
        },
        {
          "title": "Extremely Loud and Incredibly Close",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Weinstein's other big awards-season push that year."
        },
        {
          "title": "Midnight in Paris",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Woody Allen's awards run, a lot more complicated in hindsight."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Descendants",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Alexander Payne's Oscar movie, also complicated in hindsight by the Rose McGowan allegation against him."
        },
        {
          "title": "War Horse",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "one of two Spielberg movies this year, and not among his best."
        },
        {
          "title": "The Adventures of Tintin",
          "year": 2011,
          "note": "Spielberg's other 2011 release."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
